posts.title: [Tariffs] I'm Canadian, and I have to admit Trump is right. Here's why.
posts.content:
In Quebec, if you want to park your kid for a day while you go to work, it will cost you... $7.

Not per hour. Per day.

The "kid education technician" (yes, you read that right) is limited to 6-8 kids, so that's at most $56 in revenue. Of course she needs to pay the rent, electricity, toys, food, care items, etc. She needs to account for profit, tax preparation fees, maintenance and so on

All this to say, 90% of the cost of this daycare comes from the government. And where does the government take that money? Well, basically, Alberta. The rest of Canada pays for this garbage. If you live in Alberta, you will be paying 2,000$ a month for daycare. Maybe more. In Quebec, you will pay around $200 - tax deductible.

What's my point? Other people have been paying for Quebec's shit for a LONG time. This includes our industries, which are protected by this soycialist government:

  1. Aluminium companies get almost free electricity.
  2. Lumber is protected and financed by the government.
  3. Dairy, let's not even talk about this, it's THAT bad.
  4. Quebec also protects its maple syrup industry, etc.
  5. Government gives huge tax breaks to MANY industries; for instance, Ubisoft would have been losing money for 15+ years without government grants
  6. Oil, potash, mining product et al. are also highly, highly subventioned by the government

This is critically unfair to the US and I am respectable enough to admit. The US cannot compete with Canada, in Canada, under those conditions. That's not even counting the fact we constantly weaken our dollar to make our exports more attractive.

The US doesn't get all of that. And they get a huge trade deficit from us (and others, of course). And it's not fair, and it's unsustainable.

All newspapers/journalists are flipping out here, you should see, it's beautiful to see. Our premier just said this would cost us 160,000 jobs, or around 5% of our work force (LOL). We are warned food will massively go up as we import fruits et al. from the US. From our counter tariffs on your product, btw.

And all I can say is: I don't care. Canada is a socialist shithole and it's crumbling apart. Trump is right to tariff us. It's not fair that our "free healthcare", childcare and so on are being paid for by exploiting the US. Someone will say it.
